Teacher Appreciation Week is coming up next week (April 27th-May 1st). Although we have been away from school for several weeks, we still want to show our teachers how much we appreciate all their hard work during the school year and during this distance learning adventure we've all been on.

We've attached a card you may fill out and turn in with your homework Wednesday, April 29th. If you'd like to make your own card, do it!

We hope everyone is staying safe and healthy.

Thank you,

Connor Academy PTO

post_text:
Parents:

During this time of year, we typically see an increase in various seasonal illnesses. Please review with your students the following standard precautions and guidelines:

Clean or dispose of articles soiled with nose and throat discharges and wash hands after handling such articles.
Do not to share items that may be contaminated with saliva such as beverage containers.

Cover your mouth with tissue when coughing or sneezing. If no tissue is available, encourage students to “catch your cold in your elbow” by covering their mouth and nose with the crook of their arm and coughing or sneezing into their shirt or coat sleeve. Encourage proper hand washing techniques.

Children who have a fever should be kept home to rest and return when he or she has been fever free without medication for 24 hours.
text:
Parents:

During this time of year, we typically see an increase in various seasonal illnesses. Please review with your students the following standard precautions and guidelines:

Clean or dispose of articles soiled with nose and throat discharges and wash hands after handling such articles.
Do not to share items that may be contaminated with saliva such as beverage containers.

Cover your mouth with tissue when coughing or sneezing. If no tissue is available, encourage students to “catch your cold in your elbow” by covering their mouth and nose with the crook of their arm and coughing or sneezing into their shirt or coat sleeve. Encourage proper hand washing techniques.

Children who have a fever should be kept home to rest and return when he or she has been fever free without medication for 24 hours.

post_text:
We hope that you are enjoying the efficiency and convenience of using Venmo for payments to the school! In order to properly credit each student, the subject line needs to have 3 things in it:

Student name, Teacher name/grade, and Field Trip/Reason for payment.

That's it. We recognize that Venmo often uses emojis in the subject line, but these come in as jumbled text and have to be individually hand edited. Also, each field trip/item should be a separate payment, (e.g., two separate payments for Basketball and the Skiing Field Trip).

Let us know if you have any questions - thanks!
